1
00:01:36,620 --> 00:01:39,979
[NORTHWARD]

2
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:42,030
[Episode 31]

3
00:02:14,340 --> 00:02:15,590
Hit me all you want.

4
00:02:15,590 --> 00:02:17,390
I won't fight back. Come on.

5
00:02:20,590 --> 00:02:22,460
Does it kill you to

6
00:02:22,490 --> 00:02:24,200
stay out of trouble?

7
00:02:28,060 --> 00:02:29,470
You didn't even ask me why.

8
00:02:29,470 --> 00:02:31,000
I don't care why!

9
00:02:31,030 --> 00:02:32,190
You beat someone up

10
00:02:32,190 --> 00:02:33,680
and they posted it online right away!

11
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:35,280
I had a hard time stopping it from trending!

12
00:02:35,310 --> 00:02:36,360
He didn't see us as human.

13
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,430
He deserved it!

14
00:02:38,410 --> 00:02:39,470
Shao Xingchi.

15
00:02:39,940 --> 00:02:41,300
Even now,

16
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:43,320
do you still not get the severity of the situation?

17
00:02:43,350 --> 00:02:44,460
I'm ignorant.

18
00:02:44,490 --> 00:02:45,630
I don't understand the strange rules

19
00:02:45,630 --> 00:02:46,870
of your big company!

20
00:02:48,050 --> 00:02:48,820
Then

21
00:02:48,850 --> 00:02:49,800
you can ask me.

22
00:02:49,820 --> 00:02:50,820
Forget it, Xie Wanghe.

23
00:02:51,620 --> 00:02:53,320
I wish you'd hear me out instead.

24
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:56,650
Go ahead.

25
00:02:56,670 --> 00:02:57,340
I'm listening.

26
00:02:57,370 --> 00:02:59,040
Let's hear what grievances you have.

27
00:02:59,060 --> 00:02:59,920
I hope

28
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,280
that everyone who follows me

29
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:03,770
can be treated as human beings,

30
00:03:03,970 --> 00:03:05,150
be accepted

31
00:03:05,190 --> 00:03:06,430
and respected.

32
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:07,690
But you...

33
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:10,360
you just treat them as tools

34
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,840
for profit and expanding capital.

35
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:13,690
And then?

36
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:17,270
You weren't like this before.

37
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:19,800
You were tough on the outside but soft-hearted.

38
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,990
You were kind to everyone!

39
00:03:21,310 --> 00:03:22,800
I thought even if nobody understood me,

40
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:23,800
you would!

41
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:24,810
So what?

42
00:03:29,220 --> 00:03:30,730
We can't talk if you're going to be like this.

43
00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:34,079
Listen up.

44
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:35,230
Do you know

45
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:36,810
how many job opportunities

46
00:03:36,910 --> 00:03:39,740
Bee alone provides in a year?

47
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:41,190
Do you know how many people

48
00:03:41,210 --> 00:03:43,240
make a living by delivering food?

49
00:03:43,260 --> 00:03:44,740
I understand you have a kind heart,

50
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:47,390
but you can't be selfish!

51
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:49,290
Back then,

52
00:03:49,710 --> 00:03:51,360
you said you wanted to be the station chief.

53
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:53,310
I used stock options as collateral

54
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,280
to make that happen.

55
00:03:54,710 --> 00:03:55,770
But what did you do?

56
00:03:56,829 --> 00:03:59,270
You led everyone with a heart of gold

57
00:03:59,720 --> 00:04:00,930
and almost

58
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:02,990
ran the station into the ground.

59
00:04:03,010 --> 00:04:05,240
And your subordinates couldn't make money!

60
00:04:05,270 --> 00:04:06,810
All you talk about is making money.

61
00:04:07,230 --> 00:04:09,530
What about your conscience?

62
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:11,090
Is making money that important?

63
00:04:12,340 --> 00:04:13,900
When you're very rich,

64
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,950
you have the luxury to think money isn't important.

65
00:04:16,649 --> 00:04:17,950
But when everyone

66
00:04:17,980 --> 00:04:19,570
is waiting for their next meal,

67
00:04:19,589 --> 00:04:20,320
money

68
00:04:20,350 --> 00:04:21,519
is very important!

69
00:04:25,140 --> 00:04:25,910
I know

70
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:28,160
you mean well.

71
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:29,610
And then?

72
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:31,500
They don't appreciate it.

73
00:04:33,820 --> 00:04:34,810
Then you

74
00:04:34,909 --> 00:04:36,200
pity their misfortune

75
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,770
and bemoan their lack of ambition.

76
00:04:38,130 --> 00:04:40,610
You feel your well intentions are being treated like dirt.

77
00:04:40,740 --> 00:04:43,070
Do you feel particularly wronged?

78
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:44,440
Delivery riders are humans too.

79
00:04:45,470 --> 00:04:46,850
They also need care

80
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:48,159
and someone to protect

81
00:04:48,180 --> 00:04:49,210
their legal rights,

82
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:49,920
you know?

83
00:04:49,950 --> 00:04:51,310
Did I withhold their pay?

84
00:04:53,270 --> 00:04:56,450
I even enhanced their commission and rewards!

85
00:04:57,750 --> 00:04:59,190
I provide job opportunities.

86
00:04:59,210 --> 00:05:00,770
If they take the job, they have to work.

87
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,060
If they don't like it, they can leave.

88
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:04,050
No one is forcing them to work themselves to death.

89
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:06,100
The rules you set are inducing them to do that,

90
00:05:06,130 --> 00:05:06,970
you know?

91
00:05:09,390 --> 00:05:10,680
Listen up.

92
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:13,810
In a competitive society,

93
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:15,560
you're compensated according

94
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,630
to the effort you put in.

95
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:19,710
We're adults now!

96
00:05:19,740 --> 00:05:21,740
We're not kids playing house!

97
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:24,500
We still can't satisfy everyone!

98
00:05:26,220 --> 00:05:27,370
Shao Xingchi.

99
00:05:28,060 --> 00:05:29,700
We're both Beijing drifters.

100
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:31,780
After all these years,

101
00:05:31,980 --> 00:05:34,430
you know how much we've suffered.

102
00:05:35,590 --> 00:05:37,700
That's why I especially treasure this opportunity.

103
00:05:37,730 --> 00:05:38,780
I want to do a good job

104
00:05:38,810 --> 00:05:40,130
and prove myself.

105
00:05:40,650 --> 00:05:41,880
But what about you?

106
00:05:42,290 --> 00:05:44,580
With the opportunity I fought hard for,

107
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,040
you want to realize a utopia.

108
00:05:46,070 --> 00:05:46,750
No problem.

109
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:47,800
I support you.

110
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:50,070
I hope your dreams come true.

111
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:51,270
But...

112
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:56,060
use your own money and resources to play house

113
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,330
from now on.

114
00:05:58,540 --> 00:06:00,300
I wish you success!

115
00:06:41,940 --> 00:06:43,050
Where are you?

116
00:06:45,690 --> 00:06:46,330
What are you doing?

117
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:47,630
Where are you?

118
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:48,750
I'll come find you.

119
00:06:49,740 --> 00:06:50,390
Don't.

120
00:06:51,970 --> 00:06:53,290
Where are you?

121
00:06:56,550 --> 00:07:03,950
[Haikuo]

122
00:06:57,330 --> 00:06:58,570
Guess.

123
00:06:59,159 --> 00:07:00,720
I'll tell you if you guess right.

124
00:07:59,940 --> 00:08:01,000
What's wrong with you?

125
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:03,300
We broke up.

126
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:06,240
Who dumped whom?

127
00:08:07,940 --> 00:08:09,180
What do you think?

128
00:08:10,180 --> 00:08:10,910
Why?

129
00:08:16,450 --> 00:08:17,280
Speak up.

130
00:08:21,230 --> 00:08:23,130
Because I'm poor.

131
00:08:23,870 --> 00:08:25,160
What else could it be?

132
00:08:25,210 --> 00:08:27,230
Did you tell her you have stock options now?

133
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:31,130
Do I need money to keep her?

134
00:08:31,150 --> 00:08:32,850
What else do you think you could rely on?

135
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:34,179
Your good looks?

136
00:08:34,659 --> 00:08:35,870
Your abs?

137
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:36,809
Do you have any?

138
00:08:38,270 --> 00:08:40,080
Stop trying to test human nature.

139
00:08:40,870 --> 00:08:41,750
It's pointless.

140
00:08:46,930 --> 00:08:47,880
Cut the crap.

141
00:08:48,580 --> 00:08:49,490
What's the matter?

142
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,690
Xingchi and I...

143
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:00,470
fell out.

144
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:05,110
Aren't you surprised?

145
00:09:08,290 --> 00:09:10,430
How many times have you two fallen out?

146
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:12,350
And you always say,

147
00:09:12,380 --> 00:09:14,330
"I'll never see him again!"

148
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:15,770
And what happens?

149
00:09:20,510 --> 00:09:21,240
This time

150
00:09:23,140 --> 00:09:24,280
might be different.

151
00:09:32,260 --> 00:09:33,270
This incident

152
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,480
has seriously

153
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:36,480
damaged our company's image.

154
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:39,040
Public opinion is spreading the issue.

155
00:09:39,590 --> 00:09:40,200
Mr. Meng.

156
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,000
Come in.

157
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:53,390
The Series D funding was about to be finalized,

158
00:09:53,420 --> 00:09:55,060
but because of Shao Xingchi's incident,

159
00:09:55,870 --> 00:09:57,120
it's been delayed again.

160
00:09:59,180 --> 00:09:59,940
I'm sorry.

161
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,320
He's already resigned.

162
00:10:04,090 --> 00:10:05,120
As for his issue,

163
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:06,440
I'll handle it appropriately.

164
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,270
It's about time.

165
00:10:09,290 --> 00:10:10,630
That bastard

166
00:10:10,660 --> 00:10:12,590
is a bad apple.

167
00:10:15,030 --> 00:10:15,750
Alright.

168
00:10:19,140 --> 00:10:19,870
Let's talk business.

169
00:10:23,170 --> 00:10:24,090
Lately,

170
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:27,160
the competition with Yuntu has intensified.

171
00:10:27,390 --> 00:10:28,220
The pressure is immense.

172
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:30,250
I plan to apply for subsidies.

173
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,770
Finally caved in, huh?

174
00:10:33,030 --> 00:10:34,390
Who was it

175
00:10:34,410 --> 00:10:36,640
who insisted on not taking subsidies?

176
00:10:37,390 --> 00:10:39,040
Times have changed.

177
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:40,300
This time, the subsidies

178
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:41,790
aren't for the delivery riders

179
00:10:42,130 --> 00:10:43,360
but for the businesses.

180
00:10:43,550 --> 00:10:45,370
We'll subsidize three to five yuan each

181
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:47,200
for businesses who've worked with us.

182
00:10:47,220 --> 00:10:47,870
Also,

183
00:10:47,950 --> 00:10:49,000
we'll require them

184
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:50,600
to sign exclusive contracts with us.

185
00:10:51,420 --> 00:10:53,570
That won't be easy.

186
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,800
I've done some research.

187
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:55,590
It's promising.

188
00:10:55,610 --> 00:10:57,930
Haikuo has analyzed it based on big data.

189
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,010
Your buddy again?

190
00:10:59,870 --> 00:11:01,020
Can we trust him

191
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:02,230
not to harm us this time?

192
00:11:02,860 --> 00:11:04,020
I firmly believe

193
00:11:04,590 --> 00:11:05,830
it'll work out this time.

194
00:11:08,540 --> 00:11:10,520
Who'll be in charge of this ground promotion?

195
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:13,620
Give me some time

196
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,600
to find someone suitable.

197
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:18,500
Don't end up choosing another buddy of yours again.

198
00:11:18,530 --> 00:11:20,570
For a big company at our level,

199
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:22,310
nepotism

200
00:11:22,340 --> 00:11:23,450
cannot happen again,

201
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:24,270
okay?

202
00:11:43,910 --> 00:11:45,220
Mr. Qiu, what's your zodiac sign?

203
00:11:45,250 --> 00:11:45,980
Dog.

204
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:48,460
No wonder.

205
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:52,350
What do you mean?

206
00:11:55,290 --> 00:11:56,230
You bark madly

207
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:58,160
and like to bite people.

208
00:11:58,900 --> 00:12:00,120
Have you had your shots?

209
00:12:04,570 --> 00:12:05,600
Xie Wanghe.

210
00:12:06,740 --> 00:12:08,030
Are you okay?

211
00:12:09,550 --> 00:12:11,960
Do you believe I can bite you to death?

212
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:13,880
Mr. Qiu.

213
00:12:14,970 --> 00:12:16,160
In the business world,

214
00:12:16,530 --> 00:12:17,950
it's about capabilities.

215
00:12:18,860 --> 00:12:21,310
Tattling not only fails to accomplish anything

216
00:12:22,210 --> 00:12:23,680
but also makes others look down on you.

217
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:27,510
I agree.

218
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:30,890
I know I'm not very capable.

219
00:12:31,330 --> 00:12:34,670
If I can't succeed, I'll make sure you don't either.

220
00:12:35,860 --> 00:12:37,140
Behave yourself.

221
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,390
Don't you dare cross me.

222
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:56,260
[He Tianming]

223
00:12:57,680 --> 00:12:58,200
Hello?

224
00:12:58,860 --> 00:12:59,390
Mr. Xie.

225
00:12:59,410 --> 00:13:01,080
There's trouble at the station. Come quickly!

226
00:13:02,170 --> 00:13:03,070
Guys!

227
00:13:03,090 --> 00:13:04,370
We're done here. Let's go!

228
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:05,390
All of you, come back!

229
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:08,550
You can't leave!

230
00:13:08,630 --> 00:13:09,120
Move!

231
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:09,750
Move, don't stop me!

232
00:13:09,750 --> 00:13:10,320
Get off!

233
00:13:10,390 --> 00:13:10,750
Get off the bike!

234
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:11,400
Let go!

235
00:13:11,420 --> 00:13:12,000
Move!

236
00:13:12,030 --> 00:13:13,390
What's all this fuss about?

237
00:13:13,410 --> 00:13:13,970
Mr. Xie.

238
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:14,550
I quit!

239
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:15,390
Why can't I leave?

240
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:16,420
This bike isn't yours!

241
00:13:16,510 --> 00:13:17,390
You didn't stop the others.

242
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:18,440
Why just me?

243
00:13:19,970 --> 00:13:20,760
What's going on?

244
00:13:20,790 --> 00:13:21,560
Mr. Xie.

245
00:13:26,020 --> 00:13:27,150
It's like this.

246
00:13:27,180 --> 00:13:28,420
You... Get back!

247
00:13:28,450 --> 00:13:29,260
Explain!

248
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:31,900
After Station Chief Shao's incident,

249
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,350
many riders quit

250
00:13:33,370 --> 00:13:34,650
and even took the bikes with them.

251
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:36,070
Back then,

252
00:13:36,130 --> 00:13:37,860
Station Chief Shao didn't collect

253
00:13:37,950 --> 00:13:38,950
deposits from them

254
00:13:38,980 --> 00:13:40,170
as they were young and poor.

255
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,730
Are you serious?

256
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:43,580
Before,

257
00:13:43,690 --> 00:13:45,370
Station Chief Shao vouched for them.

258
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:47,370
I think he can get them back.

259
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:48,620
He has resigned.

260
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:52,730
Now,

261
00:13:53,370 --> 00:13:54,850
you'll be the chief of Station 203.

262
00:13:55,540 --> 00:13:56,360
I can't do it.

263
00:13:56,390 --> 00:13:57,800
It's not up to you!

264
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:01,470
[Top Ten Exemplary Stations in China]

265
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:02,210
Bravo!

266
00:14:01,590 --> 00:14:02,230
[Fenghua Express]

267
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:02,770
[Loading Area]

268
00:14:05,290 --> 00:14:06,680
Bravo, bravo.

269
00:14:06,820 --> 00:14:07,580
Xia.

270
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:08,610
Congrats.

271
00:14:09,170 --> 00:14:10,090
Thank you, Mr. Luo.

272
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:12,130
Bravo!

273
00:14:14,930 --> 00:14:16,240
The company

274
00:14:16,260 --> 00:14:17,710
not only gave your station

275
00:14:17,740 --> 00:14:18,810
a certificate of honor

276
00:14:18,830 --> 00:14:20,830
but also awarded you 100,000 yuan.

277
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:23,500
-Bravo!
-Thank you.

278
00:14:20,950 --> 00:14:27,210
[RMB 100,000]

279
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:24,310
That's great!

280
00:14:24,340 --> 00:14:25,100
Bravo!

281
00:14:28,970 --> 00:14:29,730
Xia.

282
00:14:30,300 --> 00:14:32,300
Don't bother. I'll be off soon.

283
00:14:32,820 --> 00:14:33,580
Why the rush?

284
00:14:33,630 --> 00:14:34,320
Thank you.

285
00:14:34,610 --> 00:14:35,610
Besides giving you

286
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:37,640
the bonus and certificate,

287
00:14:37,660 --> 00:14:39,090
I'm here on behalf of the company

288
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:40,590
to invite you back to HQ

289
00:14:40,610 --> 00:14:41,900
to conduct training

290
00:14:41,930 --> 00:14:42,720
with your experience

291
00:14:42,740 --> 00:14:43,900
on business management.

292
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:46,610
Is it long-term or...

293
00:14:47,850 --> 00:14:48,540
Let's sit and talk.

294
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:49,760
It's like this.

295
00:14:51,020 --> 00:14:53,710
Be it the training or the PR department,

296
00:14:53,740 --> 00:14:55,230
you can join anytime

297
00:14:55,590 --> 00:14:57,380
to take charge of culture development.

298
00:14:57,410 --> 00:14:59,410
The senior management came to a unanimous consensus

299
00:14:59,430 --> 00:15:01,550
that you're the best candidate.

300
00:15:04,620 --> 00:15:06,140
I really want to go.

301
00:15:07,970 --> 00:15:08,780
You have concerns?

302
00:15:09,670 --> 00:15:10,900
Don't worry

303
00:15:11,060 --> 00:15:12,230
about the compensation.

304
00:15:12,260 --> 00:15:13,810
It'll definitely be improved.

305
00:15:14,850 --> 00:15:15,660
I don't have concerns.

306
00:15:16,340 --> 00:15:17,410
I have to go back to my hometown.

307
00:15:17,630 --> 00:15:18,360
Your hometown?

308
00:15:18,900 --> 00:15:19,980
Honghuai City

309
00:15:20,170 --> 00:15:21,080
in Jiangsu.

310
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:22,890
A small city by the canal.

311
00:15:25,050 --> 00:15:26,390
Why so sudden?

312
00:15:27,190 --> 00:15:29,520
Did something happen at home?

313
00:15:30,890 --> 00:15:32,440
I've been drifting in Beijing for too long.

314
00:15:33,230 --> 00:15:34,350
I feel a bit empty.

315
00:15:35,790 --> 00:15:36,790
But thank you,

316
00:15:37,070 --> 00:15:38,900
and I appreciate the company's recognition.

317
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,400
This certificate

318
00:15:41,530 --> 00:15:43,860
[Certificate of Honor]

319
00:15:42,090 --> 00:15:43,980
puts a perfect end

320
00:15:44,440 --> 00:15:45,910
to my life as a Beijing drifter.

321
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:52,760
[Fenghua Express]

322
00:15:57,680 --> 00:15:59,330
Are you getting a promotion?

323
00:16:01,910 --> 00:16:02,910
But I didn't agree.

324
00:16:05,010 --> 00:16:06,330
Why not?

325
00:16:07,010 --> 00:16:09,830
I have more important things to do here.

326
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:10,990
Auntie,

327
00:16:11,010 --> 00:16:12,420
add two more main dishes for dinner.

328
00:16:12,450 --> 00:16:13,180
Let's celebrate.

329
00:16:13,230 --> 00:16:14,020
Sure.

330
00:16:14,050 --> 00:16:15,150
What do you want to eat?

331
00:16:15,790 --> 00:16:16,630
I'm fine with anything.

332
00:16:16,650 --> 00:16:17,830
Make something everyone likes.

333
00:16:17,860 --> 00:16:19,120
Mom, Fenghua.

334
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:19,960
Tianming?

335
00:16:20,290 --> 00:16:21,790
Back so early?

336
00:16:21,790 --> 00:16:23,260
Xingchi is in trouble.

337
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:40,180
Eating fried bean sauce noodles in a bar.

338
00:16:40,340 --> 00:16:41,410
What refined taste.

339
00:16:47,910 --> 00:16:48,630
What's wrong?

340
00:16:50,510 --> 00:16:52,240
Xie Wanghe came here last time too.

341
00:16:53,510 --> 00:16:54,870
He said the same thing as you.

342
00:16:59,910 --> 00:17:01,510
Don't tell me you're here to...

343
00:17:02,090 --> 00:17:03,560
help us patch things up?

344
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:07,480
I'm not that idle.

345
00:17:11,230 --> 00:17:12,410
He and I...

346
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:14,270
haven't been in touch for a long time.

347
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:20,030
Why?

348
00:17:21,790 --> 00:17:22,480
We're busy.

349
00:17:25,329 --> 00:17:27,670
But weren't you two...

350
00:17:29,110 --> 00:17:29,970
Weren't what?

351
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:35,770
Nothing.

352
00:17:38,070 --> 00:17:40,340
Xie Wanghe and I just aren't friends anymore.

353
00:17:40,510 --> 00:17:41,520
We're not enemies.

354
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,400
That's just how it is.

355
00:17:48,990 --> 00:17:51,000
So what do you want to do next?

356
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,720
I have a buddy who opened a shop,

357
00:17:55,420 --> 00:17:56,680
modifying off-road vehicles.

358
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:57,590
I want to give it a try.

359
00:17:58,330 --> 00:17:59,110
Is it profitable?

360
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,310
I don't know. We'll see.

361
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:07,200
How about...

362
00:18:08,110 --> 00:18:09,350
you come work with me?

363
00:18:20,270 --> 00:18:23,390
First, when loading, put small items inside the vehicle

364
00:18:23,420 --> 00:18:25,200
and secure large items on the roof.

365
00:18:25,220 --> 00:18:25,920
Second,

366
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:28,750
during scanning, pay attention to sorting loose items

367
00:18:28,830 --> 00:18:30,040
and residential items.

368
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,160
Third,

369
00:18:30,210 --> 00:18:34,170
[Sorting Area (Urban Area)]

370
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,400
report problems you can't solve

371
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:34,270
to the problem department promptly.

372
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:35,320
It's that simple.

373
00:18:35,350 --> 00:18:37,190
I believe you'll be set in one afternoon.

374
00:18:36,950 --> 00:18:40,050
[Zhongguancun South Road]

375
00:18:38,710 --> 00:18:40,740
Ms. Xia, you really want to recruit me, huh?

376
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:44,360
What, you want to back out?

377
00:18:44,390 --> 00:18:45,330
I wouldn't dare.

378
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:47,890
Then get to work.

379
00:18:49,070 --> 00:18:50,930
If you don't do well, you won't get dinner tonight.

380
00:18:53,010 --> 00:18:54,530
You've really been a boss for too long.

381
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:55,850
You're getting more and more

382
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:57,230
like Liang's dad.

383
00:18:59,350 --> 00:19:03,020
[Fenghua Express]
[Express delivery makes your life more efficient]

384
00:18:59,550 --> 00:19:01,420
Okay, okay. I was wrong, I was wrong.

385
00:19:01,450 --> 00:19:02,540
Do you surrender?

386
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:03,230
I surrender!

387
00:19:03,260 --> 00:19:04,290
You're breaking my neck!

388
00:19:06,010 --> 00:19:07,730
If I'd known it'd be like this, I wouldn't have come.

389
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:09,220
Even more brutal than Xie Wanghe.

390
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:11,000
Brutal?

391
00:19:13,090 --> 00:19:14,290
Wanghe?

392
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:15,750
You said I'm brutal?

393
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:17,400
Don't like that?

394
00:19:18,970 --> 00:19:20,240
I'll say something you'd prefer.

395
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,730
How about I call you cold-blooded?

396
00:19:22,150 --> 00:19:23,840
You can say it to my face.

397
00:19:25,230 --> 00:19:26,490
But talking behind someone's back

398
00:19:27,350 --> 00:19:28,390
isn't classy.

399
00:19:28,980 --> 00:19:33,940
[Fenghua Express]
[We're the experts in shipping parcels]

400
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:36,400
You know his temper.

401
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:38,280
Will it kill you to lay off him?

402
00:19:39,230 --> 00:19:42,500
[Fenghua Express]

403
00:19:40,460 --> 00:19:41,270
Wanghe.

404
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:42,830
Wanghe!

405
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:51,740
Wanghe, wait up.

406
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:53,280
I can't run anymore.

407
00:19:58,060 --> 00:20:00,090
Fenghua, what's wrong?

408
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:02,320
What's wrong?

409
00:20:11,350 --> 00:20:12,060
Here.

410
00:20:12,550 --> 00:20:13,550
Have some soup.

411
00:20:23,030 --> 00:20:24,010
Feeling better?

412
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:29,520
Why are you so weak now?

413
00:20:29,690 --> 00:20:32,000
Out of breath after a few steps?

414
00:20:33,980 --> 00:20:35,590
I'm just a bit anemic.

415
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:38,040
It's your fault for running so fast.

416
00:20:38,060 --> 00:20:39,360
I couldn't catch up.

417
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:40,870
I almost couldn't catch my breath.

418
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:51,310
Xingchi wasn't happy working for you,

419
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:53,160
so I asked him to come help me.

420
00:20:53,540 --> 00:20:55,070
He caused such a big mess,

421
00:20:55,590 --> 00:20:56,830
but he still won't admit it.

422
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:58,400
He's unhappy?

423
00:21:00,590 --> 00:21:01,350
Yes.

424
00:21:02,030 --> 00:21:04,310
Hitting a customer is a bit too much.

425
00:21:05,550 --> 00:21:06,420
A bit?

426
00:21:07,760 --> 00:21:09,190
It's way too much.

427
00:21:09,220 --> 00:21:10,780
If it were me, I'd fire him too.

428
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:12,360
I didn't fire him.

429
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:14,440
He resigned on his own.

430
00:21:14,470 --> 00:21:15,440
Because of this incident,

431
00:21:15,460 --> 00:21:17,320
I have to keep my head down at the company.

432
00:21:17,350 --> 00:21:19,240
I'm swamped with work stuff every day,

433
00:21:19,270 --> 00:21:21,000
and I still have to chase after bikes for him.

434
00:21:21,020 --> 00:21:22,100
Why should I have to do that?

435
00:21:24,870 --> 00:21:27,290
So you think you've done nothing wrong?

436
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:28,720
What did I do wrong?

437
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:31,400
He's your buddy.

438
00:21:31,630 --> 00:21:33,910
When he does something wrong, talk to him properly.

439
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:35,310
How else am I supposed to talk to him?

440
00:21:35,350 --> 00:21:36,550
Why does he listen to me then?

441
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:39,000
If you told him to jump off a building, he'd do it!

442
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:47,350
Fenghua, I know you mean well,

443
00:21:47,370 --> 00:21:49,000
but you can't take sides.

444
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:51,440
How am I taking sides?

445
00:21:54,510 --> 00:21:56,940
You think I'm just a heartless capitalist.

446
00:21:56,970 --> 00:21:58,580
I'm doing better than Xingchi,

447
00:21:58,600 --> 00:22:00,280
so you unconsciously assume

448
00:22:00,310 --> 00:22:01,620
that I'm bullying him.

449
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:02,370
Right?

450
00:22:02,780 --> 00:22:04,130
But I'm not.

451
00:22:04,440 --> 00:22:06,400
I'm just an employee too.

452
00:22:06,630 --> 00:22:08,630
My business card says "CEO Assistant,"

453
00:22:08,650 --> 00:22:09,540
but in fact,

454
00:22:09,570 --> 00:22:10,610
I don't even have the authority

455
00:22:10,630 --> 00:22:12,020
of a VP!

456
00:22:12,310 --> 00:22:14,510
I had to use all the credibility

457
00:22:14,720 --> 00:22:16,030
I've built up

458
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:17,950
to resolve the huge mistake Xingchi made!

459
00:22:20,270 --> 00:22:20,990
Fenghua.

460
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:24,050
You can side with your friend over reason,

461
00:22:25,250 --> 00:22:27,320
but please don't think I'm bullying him

462
00:22:27,350 --> 00:22:28,830
just because he's weaker

463
00:22:28,850 --> 00:22:30,620
and deserving of sympathy.

464
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:32,360
That's unfair to me!

465
00:22:45,820 --> 00:22:52,180
[Wankelai Supermarket Community Store]

466
00:22:48,750 --> 00:22:50,190
You're earning quite a lot.

467
00:22:50,220 --> 00:22:51,340
That's enough.

468
00:22:55,270 --> 00:22:57,110
Always rushing us. Do it yourself then!

469
00:22:57,130 --> 00:22:58,440
Or you could fine me.

470
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:01,510
Time's so tight, you know?

471
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:06,700
Some customers call me just to rush me.

472
00:23:06,940 --> 00:23:07,920
It isn't even time yet,

473
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:08,830
but they have to call me.

474
00:23:08,830 --> 00:23:09,920
Isn't that unfair?

475
00:23:13,050 --> 00:23:14,090
Xingchi!

476
00:23:14,120 --> 00:23:15,800
Why are you here?

477
00:23:16,100 --> 00:23:16,830
Xingchi.

478
00:23:16,830 --> 00:23:17,830
How have you been?

479
00:23:17,830 --> 00:23:18,920
Good. Not bad.

480
00:23:20,110 --> 00:23:21,920
Why are you eating out here?

481
00:23:21,940 --> 00:23:24,900
Um... the cafeteria is closed.

482
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:26,870
Closed? Why?

483
00:23:29,020 --> 00:23:30,870
Maybe the superiors think it wastes time.

484
00:23:31,030 --> 00:23:31,790
What?

485
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:34,820
How's having your meals wasting time?

486
00:23:35,130 --> 00:23:36,680
Besides, that cafeteria was cheap

487
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:37,850
and clean.

488
00:23:39,060 --> 00:23:39,670
Xingchi.

489
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:40,750
Since we

490
00:23:40,750 --> 00:23:42,640
go back just to eat a meal,

491
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:44,730
it wastes a lot of time on the road.

492
00:23:44,990 --> 00:23:46,750
Well, just to save a few pennies,

493
00:23:46,750 --> 00:23:49,110
it's not really worth it. So we're here.

494
00:23:54,360 --> 00:23:55,480
If you can't have a proper meal,

495
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:56,830
how can you have the energy to work?

496
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,480
Ridiculous!

497
00:24:05,090 --> 00:24:07,090
I just bought some bread and drinks.

498
00:24:08,740 --> 00:24:10,030
Have it if you're still hungry.

499
00:24:12,510 --> 00:24:13,670
[Wankelai Supermarket Community Store]

500
00:24:14,040 --> 00:24:18,240
[Wankelai Supermarket Community Store]

501
00:24:16,080 --> 00:24:16,810
Xingchi.

502
00:24:18,340 --> 00:24:19,250
Take a look.

503
00:24:22,530 --> 00:24:22,870
[Bee Delivery]
[Proposal to modify the employees' meal management]

504
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:27,130
[How to manage daily meals of employees]

505
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,090
[Notice on the implementation of employee meal subsidies]

506
00:24:27,390 --> 00:24:28,920
Is this necessary?

507
00:24:29,270 --> 00:24:31,740
Executives' meals can be invoiced and reimbursed.

508
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:33,940
Why do we have to stick to one specific restaurant?

509
00:24:33,970 --> 00:24:35,260
They offer a discount

510
00:24:35,480 --> 00:24:37,000
of 40% for bulk purchases.

511
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:38,620
We can also bring our own drinks.

512
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:40,320
More importantly, it's close to the office.

513
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:41,710
We can sign the bills right after eating.

514
00:24:41,730 --> 00:24:43,350
It saves us the reimbursement process.

515
00:24:43,980 --> 00:24:45,100
What's the point?

516
00:24:46,530 --> 00:24:48,440
Our scale is getting bigger and bigger.

517
00:24:48,470 --> 00:24:49,600
We need to simplify processes.

518
00:24:49,620 --> 00:24:51,520
Use our manpower only where it matters most.

519
00:24:55,110 --> 00:24:55,640
Alright.

520
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:57,670
In the future, for minor matters like this,

521
00:24:57,700 --> 00:24:59,060
you can decide on your own.

522
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:00,260
No need to consult me.

523
00:25:02,720 --> 00:25:03,550
Um...

524
00:25:04,930 --> 00:25:06,020
what about employee benefits?

525
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:08,200
For delivery riders?

526
00:25:08,220 --> 00:25:08,680
Yes.

527
00:25:09,390 --> 00:25:10,830
Previously, Shao Xingchi

528
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:13,500
set up a cafeteria at Station 203

529
00:25:13,750 --> 00:25:14,920
to provide boxed meals to the riders.

530
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:15,880
The results were decent.

531
00:25:16,070 --> 00:25:17,870
I want to promote this at other stations.

532
00:25:20,750 --> 00:25:23,310
He almost messed up Station 203.

533
00:25:23,590 --> 00:25:24,680
It's been proven

534
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:26,260
that his ideas are not worth following.

535
00:25:26,590 --> 00:25:28,640
It didn't increase the workers' cohesion either.

536
00:25:29,030 --> 00:25:31,310
Otherwise, when Shao Xingchi was fired,

537
00:25:31,340 --> 00:25:33,540
the station's staff would've rioted.

538
00:25:39,920 --> 00:25:40,680
Get back to work.

539
00:25:42,310 --> 00:25:43,130
Okay.

540
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:13,430
Meat skewers?

541
00:26:16,770 --> 00:26:18,330
How's your nose so sharp?

542
00:26:19,590 --> 00:26:20,960
Can't you be wrong for once?

543
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:32,200
Look at this.

544
00:26:32,490 --> 00:26:33,720
Won't you get pricked?

545
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:39,070
Stay if you want.

546
00:26:39,530 --> 00:26:41,770
If not, you can leave.

547
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:46,360
Perfect.

548
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:48,910
I'm frustrated too.

549
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:50,190
I'll drink with you.

550
00:26:50,940 --> 00:26:51,720
Come on.

551
00:27:01,240 --> 00:27:02,660
At your station,

552
00:27:03,210 --> 00:27:04,980
many delivery riders have run off.

553
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:06,690
Many bikes were taken

554
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:08,550
when they didn't pay the deposit.

555
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:10,110
Tell Xie Wanghe...

556
00:27:12,390 --> 00:27:14,400
I'll get back all the stolen bikes for him.

557
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:16,680
For those that I can't,

558
00:27:17,220 --> 00:27:19,080
I'll pay out of my own pocket.

559
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:21,210
Why don't you tell him yourself?

560
00:27:25,240 --> 00:27:26,320
No thanks.

561
00:27:27,100 --> 00:27:28,850
Even his face irks me now.

562
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:31,280
This time,

563
00:27:31,930 --> 00:27:33,500
how long do you plan to keep this up?

564
00:27:35,200 --> 00:27:36,200
For a lifetime, I guess.

565
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:39,640
Haikuo.

566
00:27:40,020 --> 00:27:41,160
Don't try to persuade me.

567
00:27:41,900 --> 00:27:42,990
Wanghe's right too.

568
00:27:43,920 --> 00:27:45,440
We came to Beijing to make money.

569
00:27:46,010 --> 00:27:47,290
But I don't think I'm wrong either.

570
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:51,420
I just want to live humanely.

571
00:28:06,780 --> 00:28:08,890
[Shuntong Express]

572
00:28:07,290 --> 00:28:08,990
Auntie, he's over there.

573
00:28:09,150 --> 00:28:10,280
Thank you, thank you.

574
00:28:09,530 --> 00:28:14,750
[Shuntong Express]

575
00:28:10,310 --> 00:28:12,610
Wang Yuan, did you get into a fight?

576
00:28:13,310 --> 00:28:15,050
Mom? Why are you here?

577
00:28:15,230 --> 00:28:16,480
Your aunt saw news online

578
00:28:16,480 --> 00:28:18,960
that said you beat up customers and got sued.

579
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:20,790
Listen to me first. Come here.

580
